Subject: larval A02g neuron
Value: Segmentally-repeated premotor neuron (Burgos et al., 2018) that is late-born in the NB2-1 Notch ON primary hemilineage (Mark et al., 2019). It is a period-positive median segmental interneuron (Burgos et al., 2018).

Subject: larval A02e neuron
Value: Segmentally-repeated premotor neuron (Burgos et al., 2018) that is late-born in the NB2-1 Notch ON primary hemilineage (Mark et al., 2019). It is a period-positive median segmental interneuron (Burgos et al., 2018).

Subject: embryonic/larval fat body region 2'
Value: Region of the larval fat body, posterior to region 1. It consists of a descending band of cells extending over the salivary gland that joins with a ventral commissure that connects to the two main lateral sheets of the fat body. There are two of these similar branches per larvae (2' and 2'').

Subject: embryonic/larval fat body region 2''
Value: Region of the larval fat body, posterior to region 1. It consists of a descending band of cells extending over the salivary gland that joins with a ventral commissure that connects to the two main lateral sheets of the fat body. There are two of these similar branches per larvae (2' and 2'').

Subject: embryonic/larval ostium 2
Value: Ostia of the embryonic/larval heart located at the A6/A7 segmental boundary.

Subject: embryonic/larval ostium 3
Value: Ostia of the embryonic/larval heart located at the A6/A7 segmental boundary.

Subject: larval antennal lobe broad duet 1 local neuron

Subject: larval antennal lobe broad duet 2 local neuron

Subject: larval antennal lobe choosy 1 local neuron
Value: One of the two choosy neuron types of the larval antennal lobe. It targets a different, but overlapping set of glomeruli. It receives most of its input from olfactory receptor neurons, other sensory neurons and picky local neurons. It outputs mainly to uniglomerular projection neurons.

Subject: larval antennal lobe choosy 2 local neuron
Value: One of the two choosy neuron types of the larval antennal lobe. It targets a different, but overlapping set of glomeruli. It receives most of its input from olfactory receptor neurons, other sensory neurons and picky local neurons. It outputs mainly to uniglomerular projection neurons.

Subject: larval antennal lobe multiglomerular projection neuron B2
Value: Multiglomerular neuron of the larval antennal lobe whose soma is located lateral to the antennal lobe. It arborizes in the antennal lobe, takes the mALT tract and projects to the region surrounding the mushroom body calyx and to the lateral horn. It receives input from a subset of olfactory receptor neurons (ORNs), a few uniglomerular olfactory projection neurons (uPNs), broad, keystone, picky, choosy, a few mPN neurons and other non-olfactory sensory neurons in the subesophageal zone.

Subject: larval antennal lobe multiglomerular projection neuron B3
Value: Multiglomerular neuron of the larval antennal lobe whose soma is located lateral to the antennal lobe. It arborizes in the antennal lobe, takes the mALT tract and projects to the region surrounding the mushroom body calyx and to the lateral horn. It receives input from a subset of olfactory receptor neurons (ORNs), a few uniglomerular olfactory projection neurons (uPNs), broad, keystone, picky, choosy, a few mPN neurons and other non-olfactory sensory neurons in the subesophageal zone.

Subject: gustatory receptor neuron A1 of the dorsal organ group
Value: Larval gustatory receptor neuron of the dorsal organ group. This neuron has a cell body in the dorsal organ ganglion and innervates the dorsal organ. There is one of these cells per hemisphere and it expresses Gr2a and Gr28a (Kwon et al., 2011).

Subject: gustatory receptor neuron A2 of the dorsal organ group
Value: Larval gustatory receptor neuron of the dorsal organ group. This neuron has a cell body in the dorsal organ ganglion and innervates the dorsal organ. There is one of these cells per hemisphere and it expresses Gr2a and Gr28a (Kwon et al., 2011).

Value: Air sac tracheoblast at the tip (leading edge) of the developing air sac primordium. It forms extensive filopodia.

Subject: adult lateral horn centrifugal neuron 6
Value: Adult neuron that receives input from MBONs of alpha lobe slice 2, and has output synapses in the lateral horn (Bates et al., 2020). There is one of these per hemisphere and it is a primary neuron (Bates et al., 2020).

Subject: adult lateral horn centrifugal neuron 7
Value: Adult neuron that receives input from MBONs of alpha lobe slice 2, and has output synapses in the lateral horn (Bates et al., 2020). There is one of these per hemisphere and it is a primary neuron (Bates et al., 2020).

Subject: adult lateral horn PV6f1 neuron
Value: Adult lateral horn output neuron that fasciculates with the PV6 primary neurite tract (Bates et al., 2020). It is a secondary neuron that is part of the DPLp1 (LHp2) medial hemilineage (Bates et al., 2020).

Subject: adult lateral horn PV6h1 neuron
Value: Adult lateral horn output neuron that fasciculates with the PV6 primary neurite tract (Bates et al., 2020). It is a secondary neuron that is part of the DPLp1 (LHp2) medial hemilineage (Bates et al., 2020).

Subject: adult lateral horn PV5g2 neuron

Subject: adult lateral horn PV5a5 neuron

Subject: adult lateral horn PV5d3 neuron
Value: Adult lateral horn output neuron that fasciculates with the PV5 primary neurite tract (Bates et al., 2020). It is a secondary neuron that is part of the CP3 (DL2) dorsal hemilineage (Bates et al., 2020). It is cholinergic (Bates et al., 2020).
